Author: HOOKER
Vol / Page:  I Flowering Plants 230
Edition:
Quote: Fagus <i>Cliffortioides,</i> Hook. fil. ... HAB. Mountains of the Northern and Middle Islands ... Very similar indeed to <i>F. Solandri,</i> and also called `White Birch', but a more alpine plant. The most alpine tree in New Zealand, covering the tops of the Nelson Mountains (alt. 6000-7000 feet) with a dense scrub ... according to Mr. Bidwill.
