Edition:
Quote: <i>Birch trees/Beech trees</i>: Bush or forest in the high country consists almost entirely of <i>Nothofagus cliffortioides</i> , the mountain beech. These were always known as birch by the early settlers, and high country men usually call them 'white birch'.
